===Etymology===
{{Gael.}} ''[[carn]]'', gen. ''[[cairn]]'', a [[heap]]: confer {{Ir.}} & Welsh ''[[carn]].''

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A rounded or conical heap of stones erected by early inhabitants of the British Isles, apparently as a sepulchral monument.
#: ''Now here let us place the gray stone of her '''cairn'''.''  -Campbell.
# {{archaic}} A pile of stones heaped up as a landmark, or to arrest attention, as in surveying, or in leaving traces of an exploring party, etc.

